  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p> </p>
<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Bormio</strong></p>
<p>Beginners are well catered for at the top of the Cable car Bormio 200,  the main nursery area with guaranteed snow. Once you are confident you can easily cross over to the more challenging runs.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Intermediate skiing in Bormio</strong></p>
<p>Intermediates will appreciate the excellent range of varied runs. Take the Bormio 2000 cable car to the summit for wide open pistes which give you some great runs back to the top of Bormio 2000 cable car or back to the village.  </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Bormio</strong></p>
<p>The Pista Stelvio one of the most exciting men's world cup downhill runs and must not be missed. The area lift pass also covers all lifts to nearby Santa Caterina and Livigno, good for days out and extending your ski area.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding holidays in Bormio<br /></strong></p>
<p>Snowboarding novices will find the steep slopes a good challenge and the terrain park is the main attraction for more experienced boarders.</p>]]></generalInformation>
